{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f06dc4aa-406a-4e8e-833f-ac3e0a117104","content":"Good news — with .NET 10 SDK, `dotnet test` uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform **by default**. The `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property was a .NET 9 opt-in and is now redundant. You can safely remove it.\n\n`EnableMSTestRunner` is still needed — it enables the MSTest runner executable entry point.","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_vZ4CxG4pYEarduQ0MHIYJd","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Removing redundant property"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"tooluse_fJusCo4VyzrC3tv8AIqcyM","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-9a4fffaee91343a7ba835e7334546858/TestProject.csproj","old_str":"    <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n    <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>","new_str":"    <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-9a4fffaee91343a7ba835e7334546858/TestProject.csproj."}],"interactionId":"ec17fd71-a9cb-4bca-8edd-6c2027b22a23","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is on .NET 10 SDK (10.0.100) and is using MSTest with `EnableMSTestRunner` and `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` set to true.\n\nIn .NET 10, `dotnet test` natively uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP) as the default test runner. The `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property was needed in .NET 9 to opt into the MTP integration with `dotnet test`, but in .NET 10 it's no longer necessary because MTP is the default.\n\nLet me provide the guidance:\n\n\nSince `dotnet test` now uses MTP by default in .NET 10, they can remove the `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property, but they should keep `EnableMSTestRunner` because that's what generates the MSTest runner through source generation.","outputTokens":539,"requestId":"2870:2B9ABB:164C6D2:17B399E:6A046009"},"id":"4b902958-cd9b-40d5-b48d-f13dfa74a466","timestamp":"2026-05-13T11:28:15.921Z","parentId":"2e456adb-b